Re: https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/DOC/Content+Anonymiser+for+Data+Backups

Following this process to clean {{entities.xml}}, rename it to {{cleaned.xml}} and re-archive it into a backup file results in an unusable backup file because the restoration process expects a the xml file to be named {{entities.xml}}. I tested this in versions 5.8.10 and 5.9.1. 

_IF_ the purpose of this document is to create a new backup file with anonymised content (which is not clear in the documentation), then after step 4 we should add an additional step, something like:

{quote}
4.5. Backup the previous version of {{entities.xml}} to a new location, and rename {{cleaned.xml}} to {{entities.xml}}
{quote}

And then step 5 should be modified to reflect that new step:

{quote}
5. Re-ZIP the new entities.xml with its exportDescriptor.properties (and any other backup files from the archive) to ensure we (eg. Atlassian Support) know exactly which version of Confluence the XML backup came from.
{quote}

